    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>den 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> September 1850</date></p>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">N. Ottinger</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaack Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi></add></p> 
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>N Y</placeName> <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Sept. 1850</date></p>
			<p>He who grants life to all living may he grant<lb/> all that is good to my friend&#44; <persName>Rabbi Isaac</persName>.<lb/> I received your letter and note that<lb/> you are again sending me prayer books<lb/> and pentateuchs&#44; but I have not<lb/> yet received them. I cannot wait&#44;<lb/> and send you eight dollars as<lb/> you request. If you have not yet<lb/> sent out the goods&#44; send it to me as<lb/> soon as possible. I want to ask<lb/> you to send me several <add>&#63;</add>&#44;<lb/> for I am in great difficulty. The<lb/> box of <add>&#63;</add> which I ordered &#189;<lb/> year ago have been taken by <persName>Mr.<lb/> Karschet</persName> and I cannot provide<lb/> for <del>the</del> <placeName>NY</placeName> communities which is to</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>me a great loss. If&#44; therefore&#44; you<lb/> can help me out&#44; send me whatever<lb/> you can spare&#44; only if they are<lb/> Kosher&#44; even though not so handsome.<lb/> You will be doing me a great service.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Ready to serve you at any<lb/> time.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yours&#44; in distress&#44; and<lb/> wishing you a happy New Year.</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">N. Ottinger</persName>.</p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
